{{Infobox Museum |name = Cayman Islands National Museum |image = CaymanIslandsNationalMuseum.png |caption = Museum logo |imagesize = 200 |map_type = |coordinates = {{coord|19.2941|-81.3827|display=inline}} |established = 1990 |location = [[George Town, Grand Cayman]] |type = National history, natural history |visitors = |secretary = |curator = |publictransit = |website = [https://web.archive.org/web/20110722142134/http://www.museum.ky/Content/16.htm Cayman Islands National Museum website] }}
The '''Cayman Islands National Museum''' is a [[museum]] in the [[Cayman Islands]]. It is housed in the former Old Courts Building on Harbor Drive in [[George Town, Grand Cayman]]. The museum is dedicated to the preservation, research and display of all aspects of Caymanian heritage. [[File:Cayman Islands National Museum - George Town, Grand Cayman.jpg|left|280px|Cayman Islands National Museum]] Opened in 1990, the museum's beginnings can be traced to the 1930s when local resident Ira Thompson began collecting Caymanian artifacts as a hobby; in 1979, the government purchased Thompson's collection and it now encompasses a major portion of the museum's collection. The museum contains over 8,000 items and artifacts ranging from coins to a 14-foot catboat. The Natural History Exhibit features a 3-dimensional map depicting the underwater geological formations that surround the Cayman Islands.
