Following the work of [[Pierre Larousse]] on the ''[[Grand dictionnaire universel du XIXe siècle|Grand dictionnaire Universel]]'', the '''''Grand Dictionnaire Encyclopédique Larousse''''', a ten-volume dictionary, was published between 1982 and 1985 by [[Éditions Larousse]]. It is an encyclopedia and a dictionary merged in a single alphabetical listing. Beneath the standard dictionary (meanings, usages) entry comes the encyclopedic section.

Articles are illustrated by photographs, maps, chronologies and diagrams.

