This is a '''list of past and present publications at the College of William & Mary'''. Many of them, such as ''[[The Flat Hat]]'', are funded through the College's [[student activity fee|student activities fees]]. Some, however, such as ''[[The Virginia Informer]]'', are privately funded.
The oldest extant student news sheet from [[the College of William & Mary]] is ''The Owl'', an unofficial [[publication]] with a strong Southern political slant from 1854. The only known copy is held by the [[Special Collections Research Center (Earl Gregg Swem Library)|Special Collections Research Center (SCRC) in Earl Gregg Swem Library]]. Student publications in a variety of formats are actively collected by the SCRC.
Overseeing all school-funded publications is the Publications Council.<ref>{{cite web| last =| first =| authorlink =| coauthors =| title =Student Activities — Organization, Conference, and Event Planning| work =| publisher =The College of William & Mary| date =| url =http://web.wm.edu/studentactivities/funding/council.php?svr=www| doi =| accessdate =February 8, 2009| deadurl =yes| archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20081211103342/http://web.wm.edu/studentactivities/funding/council.php?svr=www| archivedate =December 11, 2008| df =}}</ref> {{Expand list|date=February 2011}}
