e weekly. It is funded partially through the Publications Council, a body composed of college administrators and the editors of other campus publications. The Flat Hat maintains editorial and procedural autonomy from the College. | style="text-align:center;"|<ref>{{cite web| last =| first =| authorlink =| coauthors =| title =Student newspaper wins national award| work =| publisher =University Relations at The College of William & Mary| date =November 2, 2007| url =http://web.wm.edu/news/archive/index.php?id=8393| doi =| accessdate =February 9, 2009| deadurl =yes| archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20100624220944/http://web.wm.edu/news/archive/index.php?id=8393| archivedate =June 24, 2010| df =}}</ref> | style="text-align:center;"| [http://www.flathatnews.com/] |- | style="text-align:center;"| ''{{sort|The|Gladfly}}'' | style="text-align:center;"| 2015 | style="text-align:center;"| Still active | The Gadfly is an independent leftist publication at the College of William & Mary. | style="text-align:center;"|<ref name=SCRC/> | style="text-align:center;"| — |- | style="text-align:center;"| ''{{sort|Hatter|Hatter}}'' | style="text-align:center;"| 1970 | style="text-align:center;"| 1970 | Also called ''Strike!'' Two issues were printed in the spring semester. | style="text-align:center;"|<ref name=SCRC/> | style="text-align:center;"| — |- | style="text-align:center;"| ''{{sort|High|The High Hat}}'' | style="text-align:center;"| 1930 | style="text-align:center;"| 1961 | The student newspaper of the Norfolk Division of The College of William & Mary (which has since become [[Old Dominion University]]). | style="text-align:center;"|<ref name=SCRC/> | style="text-align:center;"| — |- | style="text-align:center;"| ''{{sort|Remnant|The Remnant}}'' | style="text-align:center;"| 1989 | style="text-align:center;"| 2005 | A weekly journal of student opinion. | style="text-align:center;"|<ref name=SCRC/> | style="text-align:center;"| — |- | style="text-align:center;"| ''{{sort|Rip-off|Rip-off}}'' | style="text-align:center;"| 1974 | style="text-align:center;"| 1974 | Possibly only one issue of this newspaper. Their slogan was, "All the news that fits, we print." | style="text-align:center;"|<ref name=SCRC/> | style="text-align:center;"| — |- | style="text-align:center;"| ''{{sort|Spirit of the Living Watching}}'' | style="text-align:center;"| 2012 | style="text-align:center;"| still active | An art and art history publication interested in both scholarly and creative responses to art as well as opportunities available to students on campus. | style="text-align:center;"|<ref name=SCRC/> | style="text-align:center;"| — |- | style="text-align:center;"| ''{{sort|Straw|The Straw Hat}}'' | style="text-align:center;"| 1914 | style="text-align:center;"| 1933 | A [[summer school]] newspaper originally published in [[Dublin, Virginia]]. Later issues began to get printed on the College campus. | style="text-align:center;"|<ref name=SCRC/> | style="text-align:center;"| — |- | style="text-align:center;"| ''{{sortname|The|Virginia Informer}}'' | style="text-align:center;"| 2005 | style="text-align:center;"| 2012 | The College's second largest student newspaper and printed monthly. It was one of the only newspaper at the College that was independently funded. ''The Informer'' was officially non-partisan but known to challenge the campus establishment and have [[Conservatism in the United States|conservative]] and [[Libertarianism|libertarian]] editorials. | style="text-align:center;"|<ref>[http://flathat.wm.edu/2005-09-02/story.php?type=1&aid=12 New investigative publication debuts]; The Flat Hat, August 2005, Austin Wright.</ref><ref>[http://www.flathatnews.com/news/1188/nichol-delegates-authority ''The Flat Hat'' online: Sep 27 2007]; Maxim Lott.</ref> | style="text-align:center;"| [http://www.vainformer.com] |- | style="text-align:center;"| ''{{sort|W&M|W&M Standard}}'' | style="text-align:center;"| 2001 | style="text-align:center;"| 2006 | A conserva